'''Ganga Jamuna''' is a [[Hindu]] pilgrimage site in [[Nepal]] where a famous fair is held around the [[temple]] before three days of full moon day during the first week of November. Here is a holy stone which is highly revered by the Hindu devotees and local people. It is believed that this holy stone preserves the divine power as water originates from there.<!-- 
