'''Jonnawada''' is a village in [[Butchireddipalem]] [[mandal]], located in [[Nellore district]] of the [[India]]n state of [[Andhra Pradesh]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mandal wise villages |url=http://apland.ap.nic.in/cclaweb/Districts_Alphabetical/Nellore.pdf |website=Revenue Department - AP Land |publisher=National Informatics Center |accessdate=26 November 2014 |page=6 |format=PDF |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140327152924/http://apland.ap.nic.in/cclaweb/Districts_Alphabetical/Nellore.pdf |archivedate=27 March 2014 |df= }}</ref> It is located on the banks of river [[Pennar]].
==History== It is famous for Sri Mallikarjuna swamy and [[Kamakshi]] amma temple constructed in the year 1150.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nellore.nic.in/places.htm |title= IMPORTANT TOURISM PLACES IN NELLORE DISTRICT=}}</ref> The goddess Kamakshi is believed as an incarnation of [[Shakti]]. A 'Sri Chakram' was installed here by Sri Jagadguru Adhi Sankaracharya.
